A year ago, if I knew that i endend up at Rennes 2 in info-com, i would have been so disapointed. For the past few years I learn to express my self through different ways such as painting, drawing, writting... but the one within I was feeling the most my self was photography. First with argentic, film camera then with digital camera. To learn more about my new activity, I looked for advices on the internet and i ended up on youtube watching for hours videos of photojournalist talking about their experiences. How they have this pulsion inside of them that was always punching them to go at the nearest of History. How theY wanted to aware about situations of people we decided to not listen, through rough pictures that showes the reality we are away from. I realised that what I wanted to do is to understand the world with his dynamics, is crisis, but also human being and their behaviours.I started to do some research on Parcoursup to find what school would fit me the most, and I found a few journalist school, but unfortunately they were to far away from where i live.  I apply to the Lannion's IUT, but i got refused. Therefor my parents parents kind of pushed me to apply to this licence. So I came here with the idea that info-com was a licence about marketing and business. And to be honest I am pleasantely surprised. I really like hox the professors are expert about their subject, it is obvious but this is a real difference that I noticed compared to highschool. Also with a lot of TD, this is very concrete and we can really explore what we are actually learning. Also, with sociology, we exploring some approch of our present society that i find really interesting to understand what we, as humans are going throug, but also as individual person.
Back in time I would have been discouraged, but now I'm glad I am here.
 This webpage performs keylogginf of input typed into a textbox. In other words, when focused on the textbox belox, the page will record each tule you hit a key or select texte with your mouse. All of the data is stored locally in your machine in the DOM and is doxnloadable as a JSON file.
